{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the authors did not explicitly state whether augmentation was used in the testing set as well, as they only mentioned that the number of images increased from 2527 to 10108.",
    "A multi-layer hybrid convolution neural network (MLH-CNN) was proposed by Shi et al. (2021).",
    "MLH-CNN was tested and compared to VGG16, AlexNet, and ResNet50 on Trash-Net.",
    "Accuracy values of 92.6%, 52.2%, 73.1%, and 74.7%, respectively, were obtained.",
    "The limitation of MLH-CNN is that the undersampling method is employed to handle class imbalance problems."
  ]
}